  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/2653289ddc904ccc8e4b441890652746",
      "title": "About QMU",
      "content": "<p><img src=\"?mode=crop&amp;width=800\" alt=\"A panoramic view of QMU campus\" width=\"800\" height=\"266.6666666666667\" data-udi=\"umb://media/d9348bd929454fbca712d38d5401f705\"></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">About QMU</span></p>\n<p>We aim to shape a better world through education, research and innovation. In doing so, we enable individuals and communities to flourish. <br><br>Our person-centred approach to learning makes us stand out from other universities, along with our focus on making society better. Our academic offering also distinguishes us. We dedicate ourselves to subjects where we can provide a distinctive offering - in healthcare; social sciences; creative arts; business; management and enterprise; and primary and secondary teaching.<br><br>Outward looking, we have a strong ethos of partnership and collaboration. At our modern campus, we benefit from easy access to the centre of Edinburgh, Scotland's vibrant and historic capital city.</p>\n<p>We are pioneers in inclusiveness and we embrace people from all backgrounds.<br><br>Find out more about the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/a67713586dab42108759e724aece703d}\" title=\"History\">history of university</a>, along with information about <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/c193260b558648f29c85d69c8c088b80}\" title=\"Quality\">our governance</a>, the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/1bf80f3b042746249bae3810ecc8ca7d}\" title=\"Chancellor, Vice-Chancellor and Senior Leadership Team\">Principal and Vice-Chancellor,</a> <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/1bf80f3b042746249bae3810ecc8ca7d}\" title=\"Chancellor, Vice-Chancellor and Senior Leadership Team\">the senior leadership team</a> and <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/23ed7ab2bf2b4808b948dca16bea8636}\" title=\"Partnerships\">our collaborative partners</a>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">Subject/Centre Specific Information</span></p>\n<p>Located within the School of Arts, Social Sciences and Management, the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/6e5272fa3f544060af877ca7f121f21c}\" title=\"Psychology, Sociology and Education\">Division of Psychology, Sociology and Education</a> presently hosts a number of undergraduate and postgraduate programmes in Teacher Education.</p>\n<p>Psychology, Sociology and Education deliver some modules shared across programmes, thus enabling cross-disciplinary collaboration and the provision of robust social science degrees. Postgraduate programmes within the division include a Masters in Research (MRes) and a Postgraduate Diploma in Secondary Education in Home Economics (PGDE).</p>\n<p>Division members are research active and submit to two units of assessment in the REF, with a third (Education) being planned for the next cycle. We also support and benefit from a number of Visiting Lecturers, PhD students and Research Assistants across the three disciplines. This role would be to join this growing division and become a full and active member of the vibrant and committed team.</p>\n<p>The Division hosts the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/9e59330129ac41028d861633fdcb6a2d}\" title=\"Centre for Applied Social Sciences\">Centre for Applied Social Sciences (CASS)</a> which conducts research into social issues that affect people’s lives locally, nationally, and internationally. Its applied approach produces research that has a theoretical and practical focus and that brings together interdisciplinary expertise in addressing issues of individual and social relevance.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/5c4855f0929e4cceb1e376e37d072af1",
      "title": "The Role",
      "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=787&amp;height=263&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"Teacher reading with a group of school children\" width=\"787\" height=\"263\" data-udi=\"umb://media/5dc34b003e97461a8eb2eca309b23868\"></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">The Role</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Senior Lecturer in Teacher Education<br><br></span>School: Arts, Social Sciences and Management<br>Division: <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/6e5272fa3f544060af877ca7f121f21c}\" title=\"Psychology, Sociology and Education\">Psychology, Sociology and Education</a><br>Responsible to: Associate Head of Division</p>\n<p>Contract Basis: Permanent<br>Contract Type: Teaching and Scholarship<br>Hours: Full Time<br>Location: Edinburgh (<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/a713799de0204325bb063efbd482f213}\" title=\"Location and Getting Here\">Musselburgh Campus</a>)<br><br>Salary/Grade: Grade 8 £34,304 - £38,857 (with possible progression to £43,434)<br>Closing Date: Sunday 19th June</p>\n<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br><span class=\"lead\">The role purpose</span></p>\n<p>The primary purpose of this role is to work collaboratively with an established team of academics to deliver undergraduate and postgraduate courses in the division of Psychology, Sociology and Education.</p>\n<p>In addition to a broad knowledge and understanding of the field of Teacher Education the post holder is also expected to provide the division with specific knowledge and expertise  in regard to either Psychology of Education, Sociology of Education or Childhood Studies.</p>\n<p>In addition to their teaching responsibilities, the post holder will also be required to contribute towards the administrative and operational running of the division.</p>\n<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Principal Duties</span><br><br>The duties and responsibilities listed below are intended to describe the general nature of the role. The balance between the elements of the role may change or vary over time depending on the specific needs at a specific point in time, or due to changing needs within the division/school.</p>\n<p><strong> </strong><strong>General </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>To carry out the duties of the post in accordance with University policies and procedures;</li>\n<li>To be aware of our Student Experience Strategy and to collaborate with our students as members of a community of learning in order to engender a student-centred learning experience;</li>\n<li>To maintain a safe work environment, including ensuring compliance with legislation and the undertaking of risk assessments as necessary;</li>\n<li>To contribute effectively to the administrative processes and committee structures of the Division, School and university;</li>\n<li>To work collaboratively and collegiately with colleagues and managers to deliver divisional and School objectives and make a constructive contribution to the development of the broader academic and cultural direction of the university;</li>\n<li>To develop and maintain appropriate dialogues and relationships with the subject community (academic, governmental and commercial) and its audiences, nationally and internationally;</li>\n<li>To support and contribute to developing the external profile of the School, Division, Research Centre and Programmes;</li>\n<li>To maintain own continuing professional development, responding flexibly to the changing demands of both the university and the subject field;</li>\n<li>To undertake any other duties which may be commensurate within the role and grade as requested by the Head of Division and/or Dean of School.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Teaching and Learning</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>To undertake teaching and assessment at both PG and UG level, including: setting, marking and assessing coursework and examinations and provide appropriate feedback to students in line with university procedures;</li>\n<li>Contribute to ensuring that the curriculum is relevant, current and meeting the needs of both students and employers;</li>\n<li>To regularly collect, and respond to, student feedback;</li>\n<li>Contribute to the supervision of undergraduate and postgraduate dissertations;</li>\n<li>Contribute to the process of curriculum development, course modification, continuous and enhanced monitoring procedures and reviews by the university;</li>\n<li>Utilise innovative approaches to teaching and learning which includes research-led teaching;</li>\n<li>To act as a personal academic tutor;</li>\n<li>To undertake administrative roles relevant to the delivery of programmes;</li>\n<li>Work with colleagues across the division and university to support course promotion, student recruitment and retention;</li>\n<li>Undertake other teaching-related administrative duties as appropriate</li>\n</ul>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/789662c6be374c56926f1027f0562c00",
      "title": "About You",
      "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=790&amp;height=264&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"Collage of QMU staff member photographs\" width=\"790\" height=\"264\" data-udi=\"umb://media/2f14e79a4ba5438bbd68fa175ffec890\"></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">About You</span></p>\n<p><strong>Please note:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>The criteria below will be assessed through the application (a), a set task (t), or interview (i).</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Please ensure that all criteria marked (a) are explicitly addressed in your application form.</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong><br>Person Specification - Essential</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A first degree in a relevant subject (a)</li>\n<li>Completed (or willing to undertake) PhD/doctorate in a relevant subject area (a)</li>\n<li>Necessary knowledge and expertise required to teach across a variety of Teacher Education modules at both UG and PG level  with an emphasis on Psychology of Education, Sociology of Education or Childhood Studies (a)</li>\n<li>Necessary knowledge and expertise required to teach across a variety of Teacher Education modules at both UG and PG level  with an emphasis on Psychology of Education, Sociology of Education or Childhood Studies (a)</li>\n<li>Experience of providing pastoral and academic support to undergraduate students (a and i)</li>\n<li>Experience of marking student assignments against agreed learning outcomes (a)</li>\n<li>Efficient time management skills (a)</li>\n<li>Experience in using IT in learning and teaching using a recognised virtual learning platform to support learning (i)</li>\n<li>Experience of applying innovative approaches in teaching and learning to enhance student experience and attainment (t&amp;i)</li>\n<li>Motivates self effectively, setting clear objectives to manage performance (i)</li>\n<li>Communicates effectively orally and in writing, adapting the message for a diverse audience in an inclusive and accessible way (a&amp;i)</li>\n<li>Plans, prioritises and manages resources effectively to achieve long term objectives (i)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Person Specification - Desirable<br></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Relevant professional/industry experience (a)</li>\n<li>Network of relevant school/professional connections (a)</li>\n<li>Experience of teaching in higher education (i)</li>\n<li>Has worked on collaborations and projects between schools and academia and actively seeks out and undertakes these in line with HEI expectations (a)</li>\n<li>Experience of conducting doctoral supervision (a)</li>\n<li>Fellowship of the Higher Education Academy, or willingness to work towards Fellowship on appointment (a)</li>\n<li>Membership of the BPS or eligibility to gain membership (<em>if psychology of education is specialism</em>)</li>\n<li>Experience of public engagement and/or knowledge exchange activity (a)</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Scottish education system (a)</li>\n</ul>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/68e99f3342704fd1a6c542e1967990f2",
      "title": "What we Offer",
      "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=793&amp;height=265&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"QMU logo in blue against a white background\" width=\"793\" height=\"265\" data-udi=\"umb://media/1dfa730a810a41c5a80408cf1a8ae78c\"></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">What we Offer</span></p>\n<p>We are committed to equality of opportunity for all by providing a supportive and flexible and inclusive working environment, and we welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds. We are proud to hold an Athena SWAN Bronze Award which recognises the advancement of gender equality at QMU.</p>\n<p>We support a flexible approach to work as well additional benefits to help your work life balance such as a generous annual leave allowance, subsidised on-site gym membership, bike to work scheme and a range of discounts.</p>\n<p>We invest in your professional development, including through access to AdvanceHE Strategic Leadership programmes and HE sector mentoring through access to TRAMS.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
